p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-=
[1.7]">This document is a technical plan for setting up and extending <stro=
ng>Claw Code</strong> =E2=80=94 what appears to be a locally-built, open-so=
urce alternative (or fork) of Claude Code, written in <strong>Rust</strong>=
.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">Here's the gist of what it covers:</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>What Claw Code is:</strong> A Rust-based CLI tool (<code cl=
ass=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 wh=
itespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">claw</code>) t=
hat interfaces with AI providers for agentic coding tasks =E2=80=94 essenti=
ally a self-hostable, hackable version of Claude Code built from source.</p=
>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>The two-track setup plan:</strong></p>
<ul class=3D"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:l=
ast-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-co=
l gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A <strong>stable copy</str=
ong> cloned from upstream, built with <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border b=
order-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.=
4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">cargo build --release</code>, authenticated=
 via OAuth, used for daily work without experimentation.</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">An <strong>experimental fo=
rk</strong> (the author's existing checkout) used as a lab for a major arch=
itectural overhaul.</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>The core of the experimental work =E2=80=94 multi-provider =
support:</strong> The current codebase is tightly coupled to Anthropic's AP=
I (auth, message schemas, transport, model aliases all Anthropic-specific).=
 The plan is to refactor it into a <strong>provider-neutral architecture</s=
trong>, introducing adapters for:</p>
<ul class=3D"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:l=
ast-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-co=
l gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Anthropic</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">OpenAI-compatible generic =
HTTP</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Google AI Studio Gemini</l=
i>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Vertex AI Gemini</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">This involves introducing a <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border bor=
der-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4r=
em] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">ProviderRegistry</code>, moving Anthropic-spe=
cific wire-format types behind a concrete adapter, and defining a provider-=
qualified model identity scheme (e.g. <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border b=
order-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.=
4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">anthropic/claude-opus-4-6</code>, <code cla=
