<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Improper acquisition, OR</=
li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Disclosure or use by someo=
ne who knew or had reason to know the information was a trade secret obtain=
ed improperly</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">That last part is doing enormous work. Someone who stumbles across =
a GitHub repository with no knowledge it contains stolen proprietary code i=
s in a very different legal position than the person who exfiltrated it fro=
m Anthropic's systems.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>The chain of liability gets weaker the further you get from=
 the source</strong></p>
<ul class=3D"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:l=
ast-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-co=
l gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The insider who leaked it =
=E2=80=94 maximum exposure, clear DTSA violation, potentially criminal unde=
r the Computer Fraud and Abuse Act</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Someone who knowingly down=
loaded it aware of its stolen nature =E2=80=94 meaningful exposure</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Someone who forked it not =
knowing its provenance =E2=80=94 much weaker case</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Someone who read it and in=
dependently reimplemented concepts from it =E2=80=94 weaker still, back to =
the tainted knowledge doctrine</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Someone who never saw it b=
ut built something functionally similar independently =E2=80=94 essentially=
 no exposure</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>GitHub itself is interesting</strong></p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">GitHub as a platform would likely be protected by DMCA =C2=A7 512 s=
afe harbor for user uploaded content, same as any hosting platform, as long=
 as they respond promptly to takedown notices. Which Anthropic would absolu=
tely send immediately.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>But here's the really important thing you're glossing over<=
/strong></p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">Remember our entire =C2=A7 102(b) conversation. Trade secret law pr=
otects the <em>specific confidential information</em> =E2=80=94 the actual =
source code, the architecture decisions, the specific implementations. It d=
oes not and cannot protect the <em>functional concepts, methods, and proces=
ses</em> those embody.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">So even in a full leak scenario:</p>
<ul class=3D"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:l=
ast-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-co=
l gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Reproducing the actual sou=
rce code =E2=80=94 copyright infringement plus potential trade secret liabi=
lity</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Using knowledge of the spe=
cific implementation to copy it verbatim =E2=80=94 trade secret liability</=
li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Understanding the general =
architectural approach and independently reimplementing it =E2=80=94 much h=
arder to pursue</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Building something that ac=
hieves similar functionality through your own implementation =E2=80=94 esse=
ntially untouchable</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>The practical reality of a GitHub leak</strong></p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">What would actually happen is this. Anthropic's lawyers would send =
DMCA takedowns within hours. GitHub would comply and take repositories down=
. Most casual users would never see it. A smaller number of people would ha=
ve forked or downloaded it before takedown. An even smaller number would ha=
ve the skill to meaningfully use raw source code.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">The people Anthropic would actually pursue would be narrow =E2=80=
=94 the leaker themselves, anyone who demonstrably extracted and commercial=
ly exploited specific proprietary implementations.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>The honest answer to your concern</strong></p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">Mass liability for thousands of GitHub users is not really how this=
 plays out in practice or in law. Companies pursue the most culpable actors=
 with the clearest damages. Suing thousands of developers who briefly had a=
 repository on their hard drive before a takedown would be a PR catastrophe=
 that would dwarf any legal benefit.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">The more realistic threat is targeted litigation against competitor=
s who demonstrably incorporated leaked proprietary code into commercial pro=
ducts. That's where the damages are real and the case is clean.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>And looping back to Claw Code one final time</strong></p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">Which is exactly why the provenance question matters so much for a =
project like that. Built cleanly from public API documentation and observab=
le behavior =E2=80=94 very strong legal position. Built with any reference =
to leaked proprietary internals =E2=80=94 suddenly in genuinely dangerous t=
erritory regardless of how many layers of reimplementation sit between the =
original and the final product.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">The law is serious about trade secrets at the source. It gets consi=
